Grateful Dead - Anthem To Beauty - 1998 [dvdrip]

A marvelous 75-minute documentary ostensibly about the making of the LPs &quot;Anthem To The Sun&quot; and &quot;American Beauty&quot;, but really covering the development of the Dead up to 1970. Includes vintage performance footage from the sixties (including Jerry being interviewed by a tuxedo-clad Hugh Hefner on &quot;Playboy After Dark&quot;) and the early seventies and many later interviews with members of the band and associates. Part of the Classic Albums video series, first broadcast in the UK in late 1997.
